1
00:00:10,051 --> 00:00:17,100
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

2
00:01:05,273 --> 00:01:08,234
Did you mean what you said
in front of my wife's grave?

3
00:01:08,318 --> 00:01:10,987
Yes, sir. I have and will
always protect your daughter.

4
00:01:11,070 --> 00:01:11,988
Make sure of that.

5
00:01:12,071 --> 00:01:13,156
You're Ninja Boy?

6
00:01:13,239 --> 00:01:14,908
You lied to me three times?

7
00:01:14,991 --> 00:01:16,201
You know, Kimberly...

8
00:01:16,284 --> 00:01:19,245
It's good that you got
to know each other better.

9
00:01:19,329 --> 00:01:21,498
Maybe it's better if you
don't see Brandon for a while.

10
00:01:21,581 --> 00:01:22,916
They're upset.

11
00:01:22,999 --> 00:01:25,168
That's why it's best
if you visit tomorrow instead.

12
00:01:25,251 --> 00:01:27,045
I'm sorry, Mom.
This is my fault.

13
00:01:27,128 --> 00:01:29,172
Our family is always
in trouble because of me.

14
00:01:29,255 --> 00:01:32,592
Son, it's time for you to stop
blaming yourself for everything.

15
00:01:32,675 --> 00:01:34,177
Mom, what are you doing here?

16
00:01:34,260 --> 00:01:35,595
Cyrus told me.

17
00:01:35,678 --> 00:01:38,765
So Kim is the one
who's been helping you cope.

18
00:01:38,848 --> 00:01:40,517
We're not doing so well
right now, Mom.

19
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:42,227
I know.
They're mad at you.

20
00:01:42,310 --> 00:01:44,103
The nerve of you to come here!

21
00:01:46,940 --> 00:01:51,236
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

22
00:01:51,319 --> 00:01:52,612
Listen, Brandon.

23
00:01:52,695 --> 00:01:54,906
You made a promise in front
of our mother's grave

24
00:01:54,989 --> 00:01:57,283
that you wouldn't hurt
our youngest sister.

25
00:01:57,367 --> 00:01:59,327
It turns out you were
just lying.

26
00:01:59,410 --> 00:02:02,539
Hey! My son is not a liar!

27
00:02:02,622 --> 00:02:04,707
- Mom. It's okay.
- But...

28
00:02:05,625 --> 00:02:08,086
- Sis.
- We're not family.

29
00:02:08,169 --> 00:02:09,587
Not anymore.

30
00:02:11,506 --> 00:02:15,134
Just please listen to what
I have to say.

31
00:02:15,218 --> 00:02:16,344
Kla.

32
00:02:17,679 --> 00:02:20,223
Brandon looks sincere.

33
00:02:20,306 --> 00:02:22,267
Let's hear him out.

34
00:02:22,350 --> 00:02:25,019
I mean, we shared good
times with him.

35
00:02:26,354 --> 00:02:30,316
If you don't want to listen
to what I have to say, then...

36
00:02:31,442 --> 00:02:32,861
please help me out.

37
00:02:34,988 --> 00:02:36,781
Let me cook that for her.

38
00:02:40,910 --> 00:02:43,204
Can you cook? Are you sure?

39
00:02:44,497 --> 00:02:45,957
Yes, a hundred per...

40
00:02:46,040 --> 00:02:47,000
- [THUD]
- Ah.

41
00:02:47,083 --> 00:02:48,126
A hundred percent.

42
00:02:48,918 --> 00:02:51,087
But Brandon...

43
00:02:51,170 --> 00:02:55,174
If you give that to Kim
and she refuses to accept it,

44
00:02:55,258 --> 00:02:56,926
or if she sends you out,

45
00:02:57,010 --> 00:03:00,013
you have to respect
our sister's wishes, okay?

46
00:03:01,764 --> 00:03:02,932
Of course.

47
00:03:07,478 --> 00:03:10,315
[WHISPERING] Kla, you
didn't have to be that harsh.

48
00:03:10,398 --> 00:03:11,733
Son.

49
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:14,819
Can you really cook that?

50
00:03:15,445 --> 00:03:17,780
Mom, I graduated
Summa Cum Laude.

51
00:03:17,864 --> 00:03:20,783
I have two master's degrees,
and I'm the vice chairman

52
00:03:20,867 --> 00:03:23,661
of the biggest pharmaceutical
company in the Philippines.

53
00:03:23,745 --> 00:03:25,622
Of course I can do this.

54
00:03:25,705 --> 00:03:32,712
[QUIRKY MUSIC PLAYING]

55
00:03:50,688 --> 00:03:57,570
[QUIRKY MUSIC CONTINUES]

56
00:03:57,654 --> 00:03:58,780
Oh.

57
00:04:00,198 --> 00:04:01,449
[BRANDON] Okay.

58
00:04:03,618 --> 00:04:10,667
[QUIRKY MUSIC CONTINUES]

59
00:04:19,133 --> 00:04:26,182
[QUIRKY MUSIC CONTINUES]

60
00:04:33,606 --> 00:04:35,775
[GROANS IN FRUSTRATION]
It's not perfect.

61
00:04:35,858 --> 00:04:38,361
Do you want us
to order food instead?

62
00:04:38,444 --> 00:04:39,779
[BRANDON] No, Mom.

63
00:04:39,862 --> 00:04:43,074
I have to do this because this
is Kim's favorite comfort food.

64
00:04:43,157 --> 00:04:44,158
Uh...

65
00:04:44,242 --> 00:04:45,910
How about I call Susan

66
00:04:45,994 --> 00:04:48,204
so she can walk you through it over the phone?

67
00:04:48,287 --> 00:04:49,872
Mom, I can do this.

68
00:04:49,956 --> 00:04:51,374
Uh, wait...

69
00:04:52,250 --> 00:04:54,210
[BRANDON] Uh...

70
00:04:54,293 --> 00:04:57,839
It's a good thing
we bought extra noodles.

71
00:05:07,223 --> 00:05:08,599
Um...

72
00:05:09,308 --> 00:05:12,270
I'll go for a bit, okay?
I have to talk to someone.

73
00:05:12,353 --> 00:05:13,438
Okay.

74
00:05:17,316 --> 00:05:19,694
Is it... water?

75
00:05:21,571 --> 00:05:23,698
[CARLOTA] Uh... Excuse me.

76
00:05:24,323 --> 00:05:25,408
Uh...

77
00:05:26,325 --> 00:05:29,704
I'm Carlota, Brandon's mom.

78
00:05:30,288 --> 00:05:31,706
Nice to meet you.

79
00:05:33,416 --> 00:05:35,209
Felix Liwanag.

80
00:05:35,293 --> 00:05:36,627
Can we talk?

81
00:05:36,711 --> 00:05:37,795
[FELIX SIGHS SHARPLY]

82
00:05:38,963 --> 00:05:40,882
It seems like
I don't have a choice.

83
00:05:42,550 --> 00:05:46,262
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

84
00:05:46,346 --> 00:05:47,764
[KIM] Ninja Boy!

85
00:05:49,390 --> 00:05:51,934
Is there something
you're not telling me?

86
00:05:52,018 --> 00:05:55,271
[KIM] I called you Ninja Boy.

87
00:05:55,354 --> 00:05:59,567
Maybe I was talking gibberish
while I was half asleep.

88
00:05:59,650 --> 00:06:01,986
He's such a liar!

89
00:06:02,653 --> 00:06:03,946
Liar!

90
00:06:04,030 --> 00:06:07,408
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

91
00:06:07,492 --> 00:06:10,745
[FIREWORKS EXPLODING]

92
00:06:11,496 --> 00:06:12,789
[SNIFFLES]

93
00:06:12,872 --> 00:06:14,415
You're such a liar.

94
00:06:15,750 --> 00:06:17,085
[SCREAMING]

95
00:06:17,168 --> 00:06:24,133
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

96
00:06:24,967 --> 00:06:26,385
[BRANDON] I'll court you.

97
00:06:27,136 --> 00:06:28,513
And I promise you.

98
00:06:29,138 --> 00:06:31,849
In two days, we'll be a couple.

99
00:06:35,019 --> 00:06:36,729
[BRANDON] Sec. Kim.

100
00:06:36,813 --> 00:06:38,606
You will get hurt.

101
00:06:38,689 --> 00:06:40,399
Even if you don't blame
Ninja Boy

102
00:06:40,483 --> 00:06:42,777
for everything that happened
with you and your mom,

103
00:06:43,903 --> 00:06:48,157
the memories he triggers
can and will hurt you.

104
00:06:49,408 --> 00:06:51,494
I want to feel whole, boss.

105
00:06:53,663 --> 00:07:00,628
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

106
00:07:06,926 --> 00:07:08,136
[SNIFFLES]

107
00:07:08,219 --> 00:07:10,638
Why did you have to do that?

108
00:07:12,431 --> 00:07:13,474
What did she say?

109
00:07:15,726 --> 00:07:19,438
She's talking to herself, Kla.

110
00:07:19,522 --> 00:07:22,483
I think she's having
a mental breakdown.

111
00:07:22,567 --> 00:07:23,818
[SNIFFLES]

112
00:07:23,901 --> 00:07:25,611
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

113
00:07:26,279 --> 00:07:27,697
Come in!

114
00:07:29,240 --> 00:07:30,283
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

115
00:07:31,159 --> 00:07:33,578
- [SQUEALS] It's Morpheus!
- Hey.

116
00:07:33,661 --> 00:07:36,122
He's the one from IdeaEx.

117
00:07:36,205 --> 00:07:38,040
He's Kim's idol.

118
00:07:38,124 --> 00:07:40,877
Hey, get a hold of yourself.
Calm down, okay?

119
00:07:40,960 --> 00:07:42,336
I know who he is.

120
00:07:42,420 --> 00:07:43,462
Hi, I'm...

121
00:07:43,546 --> 00:07:45,590
You guys are so persistent,
aren't you?

122
00:07:45,673 --> 00:07:46,757
[KIM] Kla...

123
00:07:47,550 --> 00:07:49,177
Is that Cyrus?

124
00:07:49,844 --> 00:07:51,596
I want to talk to him.

125
00:07:53,556 --> 00:07:54,599
[CHUCKLES]

126
00:08:06,027 --> 00:08:11,324
I just found out that Brandon
and Secretary Kim are dating.

127
00:08:12,617 --> 00:08:14,535
I think they're going
to break up.

128
00:08:15,995 --> 00:08:19,123
My son was just trying
to protect your daughter.

129
00:08:19,999 --> 00:08:22,001
Is that why he lied?

130
00:08:23,586 --> 00:08:26,505
Donny didn't hide the truth

131
00:08:26,589 --> 00:08:29,592
because he wanted
to deceive anyone.

132
00:08:29,675 --> 00:08:34,347
I mean, he could've said
that he was that boy.

133
00:08:36,682 --> 00:08:39,560
You would've all seen him
as a hero.

134
00:08:40,686 --> 00:08:43,606
But my son is not that
kind of person.

135
00:08:44,857 --> 00:08:49,612
He prioritized Secretary Kim's
welfare over his own.

136
00:08:50,363 --> 00:08:52,865
Her welfare? He ended up
hurting my daughter.

137
00:08:52,949 --> 00:08:54,784
My son is hurting too.

138
00:08:57,995 --> 00:09:01,582
Donny chose to be silent
even though it hurt.

139
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:05,753
He didn't want Kim to
experience what he went through.

140
00:09:06,879 --> 00:09:10,841
To this day, my son still
has nightmares.

141
00:09:11,509 --> 00:09:15,179
Every time he sees
cable ties, he...

142
00:09:15,263 --> 00:09:19,267
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

143
00:09:19,350 --> 00:09:22,270
You wouldn't want someone
you love to experience that.

144
00:09:24,188 --> 00:09:26,691
But what he did is still wrong.

145
00:09:26,774 --> 00:09:29,068
He knows, that's why he's
trying to make up for it.

146
00:09:30,236 --> 00:09:33,281
How? By stuffing my
daughter with noodles?

147
00:09:33,364 --> 00:09:35,491
He can't just buy Kim off
with that.

148
00:09:35,574 --> 00:09:38,494
He's not trying
to buy off your daughter.

149
00:09:38,577 --> 00:09:42,665
It's his way of asking
for forgiveness.

150
00:09:43,833 --> 00:09:46,043
That is, if Kim forgives him.

151
00:09:46,127 --> 00:09:48,212
I know Secretary Kim.

152
00:09:48,296 --> 00:09:51,048
- She's kind and understanding.
- I know her too.

153
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:53,884
And I also know...

154
00:09:54,844 --> 00:09:57,638
that Secretary Kim
understands...

155
00:09:58,764 --> 00:10:00,683
that no one is perfect.

156
00:10:00,766 --> 00:10:02,435
Not me.

157
00:10:02,518 --> 00:10:04,061
Not you.

158
00:10:04,145 --> 00:10:06,022
Definitely not my son.

159
00:10:07,064 --> 00:10:08,733
Unless of course...

160
00:10:10,026 --> 00:10:12,320
you haven't made
a mistake in life.

161
00:10:13,195 --> 00:10:14,905
Or you don't have shortcomings.

162
00:10:14,989 --> 00:10:18,826
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

163
00:10:18,909 --> 00:10:20,703
Mr. Liwanag.

164
00:10:23,706 --> 00:10:26,667
My sons have suffered
long enough.

165
00:10:27,710 --> 00:10:30,254
You don't need to punish them.

166
00:10:31,547 --> 00:10:34,550
They've been carrying that
trauma all their lives.

167
00:10:37,386 --> 00:10:39,055
So, please...

168
00:10:40,056 --> 00:10:41,223
be kind.

169
00:10:41,307 --> 00:10:46,354
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

170
00:10:46,437 --> 00:10:50,066
You also lied to me.

171
00:10:53,652 --> 00:10:56,447
It feels like you two
conspired against me.

172
00:10:59,116 --> 00:11:00,159
But...

173
00:11:01,410 --> 00:11:04,080
Why did you both lie to me?

174
00:11:04,789 --> 00:11:05,748
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

175
00:11:05,831 --> 00:11:11,420
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

176
00:11:11,504 --> 00:11:13,297
It started because of me.

177
00:11:16,967 --> 00:11:19,678
Brandon and I even fought
because of it.

178
00:11:21,180 --> 00:11:24,433
That's why when you showed me
my grade school essay,

179
00:11:25,184 --> 00:11:27,895
it felt like being doused
with cold water.

180
00:11:29,021 --> 00:11:31,857
It reminded me
of what I did to my family.

181
00:11:33,484 --> 00:11:35,027
Especially to Donny.

182
00:11:36,028 --> 00:11:36,904
[GRUNTS]

183
00:11:36,987 --> 00:11:38,989
- He went missing because of me.
- Help!

184
00:11:39,073 --> 00:11:41,909
[YOUNG BRANDON] Let me out!
Please!

185
00:11:41,992 --> 00:11:47,498
- [UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]
- [LOUD KNOCKING]

186
00:11:47,581 --> 00:11:51,961
I told you that you and your
brother should go home together!

187
00:11:52,044 --> 00:11:53,963
Where is Brandon?!

188
00:11:54,046 --> 00:11:59,593
Cyrus, please tell us
where Brandon is.

189
00:11:59,677 --> 00:12:01,846
We won't get mad at you.

190
00:12:01,929 --> 00:12:03,264
Tell us!

191
00:12:04,306 --> 00:12:05,391
[THUD]

192
00:12:06,308 --> 00:12:07,935
It's all clear, sir.

193
00:12:10,229 --> 00:12:12,189
[YOUNG CYRUS]
We left him here.

194
00:12:12,273 --> 00:12:13,315
Over there.

195
00:12:14,233 --> 00:12:16,944
Here? You left him here?

196
00:12:17,027 --> 00:12:17,945
[YOUNG CYRUS] Yes.

197
00:12:18,028 --> 00:12:25,035
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

198
00:12:25,744 --> 00:12:27,997
But this is where we left him.

199
00:12:29,832 --> 00:12:32,835
You shouldn't have locked him
in there in the first place!

200
00:12:32,918 --> 00:12:34,795
What kind of brother are you?!

201
00:12:38,966 --> 00:12:45,264
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

202
00:12:45,347 --> 00:12:47,183
[ROBERT] Donny, you're home now.

203
00:12:47,266 --> 00:12:49,059
Cyrus, no.

204
00:12:58,110 --> 00:13:01,071
Cyrus, dear...

205
00:13:01,155 --> 00:13:04,325
Let's not bother Brandon
for now, okay?

206
00:13:05,826 --> 00:13:08,787
[CYRUS] I felt like an outsider
in my own family.

207
00:13:09,788 --> 00:13:11,332
I was jealous...

208
00:13:12,333 --> 00:13:13,709
because of the love
and attention

209
00:13:13,792 --> 00:13:15,544
that they were giving
to Brandon.

210
00:13:16,128 --> 00:13:17,963
So I wrote that essay.

211
00:13:18,964 --> 00:13:21,050
I wrote that I was the one
who got kidnapped.

212
00:13:22,801 --> 00:13:24,220
True enough,

213
00:13:26,347 --> 00:13:28,015
my teachers...

214
00:13:29,308 --> 00:13:32,603
and classmates, they showered me
with their sympathy.

215
00:13:36,065 --> 00:13:38,859
Until Dad found out
about what I did.

216
00:13:41,779 --> 00:13:42,821
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

217
00:13:44,448 --> 00:13:45,491
After that...

218
00:13:47,076 --> 00:13:48,077
[CHUCKLES]

219
00:13:49,495 --> 00:13:51,705
I became persona
non grata again.

220
00:13:53,499 --> 00:13:56,585
That's why when I found out
that Troy was investigating,

221
00:13:56,669 --> 00:13:58,295
I had to do my part.

222
00:13:58,879 --> 00:14:00,339
For my family.

223
00:14:01,757 --> 00:14:03,926
And finally be a brother
to Brandon.

224
00:14:06,178 --> 00:14:09,139
I don't want Brandon to recall
what happened to him.

225
00:14:09,223 --> 00:14:13,435
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

226
00:14:13,519 --> 00:14:16,438
Is that why you pretended
to be Ninja Boy?

227
00:14:19,358 --> 00:14:21,735
So you could protect Brandon?

228
00:14:27,116 --> 00:14:29,159
The Park family shouldn't see

229
00:14:29,243 --> 00:14:31,537
any weakness in
Brandon's leadership.

230
00:14:32,955 --> 00:14:34,290
Uh...

231
00:14:34,373 --> 00:14:37,167
Why would they think
there's weakness

232
00:14:37,251 --> 00:14:39,962
in the boss's leadership?

233
00:14:40,045 --> 00:14:41,130
Well...[SNIFFLES]

234
00:14:41,880 --> 00:14:44,174
Trauma can manipulate
your judgment.

235
00:14:44,967 --> 00:14:47,970
Aren't you wondering why the son

236
00:14:48,053 --> 00:14:50,306
of Prime Alpha's new
partner is here?

237
00:14:51,098 --> 00:14:53,017
They'll be judging
his every move.

238
00:14:53,892 --> 00:14:57,271
And here he is,
making you a snack?

239
00:15:00,190 --> 00:15:01,233
What?

240
00:15:02,109 --> 00:15:03,444
Boss is doing what?

241
00:15:04,445 --> 00:15:08,032
[QUIRKY MUSIC PLAYING]

242
00:15:08,115 --> 00:15:09,867
Why is it still soggy?

243
00:15:09,950 --> 00:15:11,410
[HOSPITAL STAFF] Just keep
trying, sir.

244
00:15:11,493 --> 00:15:13,579
We'll take the rejects.

245
00:15:13,662 --> 00:15:15,748
We'll go now, sir.

246
00:15:19,501 --> 00:15:26,175
[QUIRKY MUSIC CONTINUES]

247
00:15:26,258 --> 00:15:28,552
Why won't it stay firm?

248
00:15:33,098 --> 00:15:35,476
You shouldn't wait too long.

249
00:15:35,559 --> 00:15:42,566
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

250
00:15:43,442 --> 00:15:45,653
You mean, in cooking noodles?

251
00:15:47,071 --> 00:15:48,906
And also in resolving conflicts.

252
00:15:53,952 --> 00:15:55,037
I'm sorry.

253
00:15:57,665 --> 00:16:01,085
I don't understand why even
though I want to get mad at you,

254
00:16:02,169 --> 00:16:03,504
my heart won't let me.

255
00:16:05,506 --> 00:16:07,633
You're so good at it.

256
00:16:08,509 --> 00:16:11,637
You see, even when I was
new to the company,

257
00:16:12,388 --> 00:16:14,181
I couldn't stay mad at you.

258
00:16:15,265 --> 00:16:17,434
What more now that
you're my boyfriend?

259
00:16:17,518 --> 00:16:21,730
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

260
00:16:21,814 --> 00:16:22,856
So...

261
00:16:24,191 --> 00:16:26,568
I'm still your boyfriend and...

262
00:16:27,695 --> 00:16:29,738
you won't break up with me?

263
00:16:29,822 --> 00:16:32,574
It feels like we've been
together for nine years.

264
00:16:34,618 --> 00:16:36,870
It's hard to let that go, right?

265
00:16:36,954 --> 00:16:37,996
[CHUCKLES]

266
00:16:40,082 --> 00:16:41,500
I love you.

267
00:16:45,254 --> 00:16:46,880
I love you too, boss.

268
00:16:49,967 --> 00:16:51,009
It's okay.

269
00:16:51,885 --> 00:16:53,345
At this point,

270
00:16:54,179 --> 00:16:56,515
I don't really care
what you call me.

271
00:16:59,351 --> 00:17:00,644
I love you too.

272
00:17:00,728 --> 00:17:07,735
["HERE WITH YOU"
BY BINI PLAYING]

273
00:17:18,787 --> 00:17:20,456
[WALTER] Yay!

274
00:17:21,373 --> 00:17:23,500
Sec. Kim is getting
discharged today,

275
00:17:23,584 --> 00:17:24,835
but she's still on leave.

276
00:17:24,918 --> 00:17:27,796
It's too bad she's not here
to join us in welcoming

277
00:17:27,880 --> 00:17:29,381
our new team member...

278
00:17:29,465 --> 00:17:30,799
Roni!

279
00:17:30,883 --> 00:17:33,927
- [CLAPPING]
- Welcome to the team, Roni.

280
00:17:34,011 --> 00:17:36,305
You know, I'm so excited
to work with you all.

281
00:17:36,388 --> 00:17:38,223
And this is a dream
come true for me.

282
00:17:38,307 --> 00:17:39,391
I swear. Legit!

283
00:17:39,475 --> 00:17:40,934
Wow. Congrats!

284
00:17:41,018 --> 00:17:42,770
- Congratulations.
- Welcome!

285
00:17:42,853 --> 00:17:44,980
Hmm. Yeah, congrats.

286
00:17:45,063 --> 00:17:48,233
Thirty-one unread emails,
and it's not even 9AM yet!

287
00:17:48,317 --> 00:17:50,944
- My gosh. Spell toxic day.
- [QUIRKY MUSIC PLAYING]

288
00:17:51,028 --> 00:17:52,362
And we have a visitor.

289
00:17:52,446 --> 00:17:54,823
I feel like we're all
under the microscope today.

290
00:17:54,907 --> 00:17:55,991
Kim Marie.

291
00:17:56,074 --> 00:17:57,826
Let me take care of it.
I'll help you.

292
00:17:57,910 --> 00:18:00,954
- Ooh.
- Oh. See? That's the spirit!

293
00:18:01,038 --> 00:18:03,165
Right? No negative vibes
this morning.

294
00:18:03,248 --> 00:18:04,583
He'll help you.

295
00:18:04,666 --> 00:18:06,043
[JORDY] Oh, wow!

296
00:18:06,126 --> 00:18:10,005
A member
of the Park family is late!

297
00:18:10,088 --> 00:18:13,926
She owns 80% of this company.

298
00:18:14,009 --> 00:18:15,260
Giving you...

299
00:18:15,344 --> 00:18:20,140
executive realness
eleganza extravaganza!

300
00:18:20,224 --> 00:18:21,600
[QUIRKY MUSIC CONTINUES]

301
00:18:21,683 --> 00:18:23,352
Don't worry, guys!

302
00:18:24,228 --> 00:18:25,521
I got this.

303
00:18:25,604 --> 00:18:29,858
I'm sure I will impress
Oppa Daniel. Hmm?

304
00:18:30,818 --> 00:18:33,445
[CARLOTA]
I defended Brandon!

305
00:18:33,529 --> 00:18:37,115
They were acting all perfect,
like they never made mistakes.

306
00:18:37,199 --> 00:18:41,286
And they made Brandon
cook instant noodles!

307
00:18:41,370 --> 00:18:44,706
To think here, we don't
order him around.

308
00:18:46,041 --> 00:18:47,793
Wait, wait. Rewind.

309
00:18:48,794 --> 00:18:52,714
You said Secretary Kim
is the one Cyrus likes.

310
00:18:54,216 --> 00:18:56,176
And it turns out
that Secretary Kim

311
00:18:56,260 --> 00:18:58,679
- is the girlfriend of Brandon?!
- Shh!

312
00:18:59,805 --> 00:19:02,015
Cyrus might hear us.

313
00:19:02,099 --> 00:19:03,934
It's heartbreaking, right?

314
00:19:04,017 --> 00:19:07,229
Like the novels
that Cyrus writes.

315
00:19:07,312 --> 00:19:08,480
Except...

316
00:19:09,189 --> 00:19:11,233
it's him and Brandon.

317
00:19:11,984 --> 00:19:14,611
But don't worry.
He said he was fine.

318
00:19:15,529 --> 00:19:19,616
Yeah, but what if this causes
a deeper rift between them?

319
00:19:19,700 --> 00:19:25,455
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

320
00:19:28,458 --> 00:19:29,793
[STAFF] Sir, ma'am.

321
00:19:29,877 --> 00:19:30,961
[QUIRKY MUSIC PLAYING]

322
00:19:31,044 --> 00:19:33,547
This is the area where we
receive our deliveries.

323
00:19:33,630 --> 00:19:35,132
Excuse me, ma'am, sir.

324
00:19:38,844 --> 00:19:40,554
Is Brandon busy with something?

325
00:19:41,388 --> 00:19:42,347
Where is he?

326
00:19:42,431 --> 00:19:45,934
Sir, our vice chairman
is on top of everything.

327
00:19:46,018 --> 00:19:47,269
He is like the wind.

328
00:19:47,352 --> 00:19:50,522
You can't see him,
but you can feel him.

329
00:19:50,606 --> 00:19:51,648
Like a ghost?

330
00:19:51,732 --> 00:19:53,358
[QUIRKY MUSIC CONTINUES]

331
00:19:53,442 --> 00:19:55,360
Anyway, I hope
everything is ready

332
00:19:55,444 --> 00:19:57,404
for the arrival of the shipment.

333
00:19:57,487 --> 00:19:58,363
Yes, sir.

334
00:19:58,447 --> 00:20:01,700
Our regulatory department
keeps us updated.

335
00:20:01,783 --> 00:20:04,119
How about the handling
of vaccine logistics?

336
00:20:04,202 --> 00:20:07,080
Everything's under control, sir.

337
00:20:07,164 --> 00:20:11,501
[QUIRKY MUSIC CONTINUES]

338
00:20:11,585 --> 00:20:14,212
I want to review
the cold chain management.

339
00:20:14,296 --> 00:20:17,049
Well, sir, we've already
mapped out the cold chain

340
00:20:17,132 --> 00:20:19,509
with your team from Seoul.

341
00:20:19,593 --> 00:20:21,887
I want to review it for myself.

342
00:20:21,970 --> 00:20:23,972
We'll send you the details.

343
00:20:24,056 --> 00:20:27,184
[QUIRKY MUSIC CONTINUES]

344
00:20:27,267 --> 00:20:29,019
[WHISPERING] What a snob.

345
00:20:30,562 --> 00:20:32,689
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

346
00:20:32,773 --> 00:20:33,857
What did you say?

347
00:20:33,941 --> 00:20:35,567
Um, no, sir!

348
00:20:35,651 --> 00:20:37,778
I said... good job!

349
00:20:37,861 --> 00:20:40,405
You're... You're
very, very good. Mm.

350
00:20:40,489 --> 00:20:41,490
Yes!

351
00:20:43,951 --> 00:20:45,661
Uh, hand it to me.
I'll take it inside.

352
00:20:45,744 --> 00:20:48,413
No, no, I've got it.
Don't tire yourself out.

353
00:20:48,497 --> 00:20:50,082
Uh, thank you.

354
00:20:51,250 --> 00:20:52,960
And don't mind me.

355
00:20:53,043 --> 00:20:56,213
I'm just here because,
knowing you,

356
00:20:56,296 --> 00:20:58,256
for sure you'll go back
to work right away.

357
00:20:58,340 --> 00:21:00,759
So I'm here to make sure
you get some rest, okay?

358
00:21:01,426 --> 00:21:03,845
- Hmm. Okay.
- [QUIRKY MUSIC PLAYING]

359
00:21:03,929 --> 00:21:06,014
Okay. Where's your tablet
or your laptop?

360
00:21:06,098 --> 00:21:08,225
I'll reply
to your email backlogs.

361
00:21:08,308 --> 00:21:11,770
No need. I talked to Kim Marie.
She'll take care of it.

362
00:21:11,853 --> 00:21:13,730
Oh. Uh, okay.

363
00:21:15,190 --> 00:21:18,527
I'm sure you're tired from
watching over me last night.

364
00:21:19,236 --> 00:21:22,322
You were up all night,
so... it's fine.

365
00:21:22,406 --> 00:21:23,907
Okay, uh...

366
00:21:23,991 --> 00:21:27,411
Ah! You can watch... TV.

367
00:21:27,494 --> 00:21:29,121
I'll just take a shower.

368
00:21:30,247 --> 00:21:31,623
- Um. Okay.
- Here.

369
00:21:31,707 --> 00:21:33,125
Do you need anything else?

370
00:21:33,208 --> 00:21:34,751
No.

371
00:21:34,835 --> 00:21:36,211
Here.

372
00:21:36,294 --> 00:21:37,295
There you go.

373
00:21:39,047 --> 00:21:42,175
Uh, it doesn't work well.
Just a minute.

374
00:21:42,926 --> 00:21:45,095
[REMOTE THUDDING]

375
00:21:45,804 --> 00:21:46,805
Um.

376
00:21:47,889 --> 00:21:50,100
There it is. High-tech, right?

377
00:21:50,183 --> 00:21:51,935
Just bang it
if it stops working.

378
00:21:52,019 --> 00:21:53,020
Okay.

379
00:21:54,104 --> 00:21:55,355
I'll go take a shower.

380
00:21:57,024 --> 00:22:01,403
Um, okay. Just let me know
if you need anything, okay?

381
00:22:01,486 --> 00:22:02,821
[QUIRKY MUSIC CONTINUES]

382
00:22:02,904 --> 00:22:04,656
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

383
00:22:04,740 --> 00:22:08,535
[INDISTINCT CHATTER ON TV]

384
00:22:11,705 --> 00:22:14,666
Thank you. My task got easier
because of your help.

385
00:22:14,750 --> 00:22:16,918
No problem. Give me more work.

386
00:22:17,002 --> 00:22:19,254
Okay, sure. Hold on.

387
00:22:20,756 --> 00:22:23,258
You know, you're very helpful.

388
00:22:23,341 --> 00:22:25,052
Unlike Daniel Park!

389
00:22:25,135 --> 00:22:27,846
He's so obnoxious. Such a snob!

390
00:22:27,929 --> 00:22:31,016
He's so uninspiring
to work with! My god!

391
00:22:32,142 --> 00:22:33,727
Good evening. [CHUCKLES]

392
00:22:33,810 --> 00:22:35,062
- Hmm?
- Baldo.

393
00:22:36,188 --> 00:22:40,692
Unlike someone here
who's the superhero of my life!

394
00:22:40,776 --> 00:22:42,486
What do you need, Baldo?

395
00:22:42,569 --> 00:22:46,573
Um, Sir asked me
to get something.

396
00:22:46,656 --> 00:22:49,117
You've been coming here
a lot lately, Baldo.

397
00:22:49,201 --> 00:22:50,994
That's right.

398
00:22:51,078 --> 00:22:52,996
It's probably not urgent, right?

399
00:22:53,080 --> 00:22:55,165
Here, have some food.

400
00:22:55,248 --> 00:22:56,792
- [BALDO] Sir?
- There's pizza.

401
00:22:56,875 --> 00:22:58,085
[BALDO] Thank you.

402
00:22:58,168 --> 00:23:00,003
Here, Baldo. Take some.
It's delicious.

403
00:23:00,796 --> 00:23:02,339
[BALDO] Uh...

404
00:23:02,422 --> 00:23:04,966
Just take it. Here.
There you go.

405
00:23:05,050 --> 00:23:06,468
Thank you.

406
00:23:06,551 --> 00:23:07,636
[QUIRKY MUSIC PLAYING]

407
00:23:07,719 --> 00:23:10,055
If he's not a snob,
he's like Pong Pagong!

408
00:23:10,889 --> 00:23:13,016
What's "Pong Pagong"?

409
00:23:13,100 --> 00:23:14,976
It means a slowpoke, girl.

410
00:23:15,060 --> 00:23:16,686
Maybe he's a Capricorn.

411
00:23:16,770 --> 00:23:19,189
They're not that in touch
with their emotions.

412
00:23:19,272 --> 00:23:21,066
That's why they act slow.

413
00:23:21,149 --> 00:23:23,485
Sir Walt, that statement
doesn't always apply...

414
00:23:23,568 --> 00:23:26,196
Are you a Capricorn?
Why are you affected?

415
00:23:26,279 --> 00:23:29,950
[QUIRKY MUSIC CONTINUES]

416
00:23:30,033 --> 00:23:32,369
Anyway, he takes so long
to make his move!

417
00:23:32,452 --> 00:23:34,913
My beauty is getting impatient!

418
00:23:34,996 --> 00:23:37,541
I'm datable. I'm a catch!

419
00:23:37,624 --> 00:23:39,376
And I don't have much patience.

420
00:23:39,459 --> 00:23:41,753
So you'd better make your move!

421
00:23:41,837 --> 00:23:43,505
The clock's ticking, boy!

422
00:23:43,588 --> 00:23:45,173
[QUIRKY MUSIC CONTINUES]

423
00:23:45,257 --> 00:23:46,633
[WHISTLE BLOWS ON TV]

424
00:23:46,716 --> 00:23:48,718
- Uh, boss?
- Hmm?

425
00:23:48,802 --> 00:23:53,515
Um, Cyrus stopped by
the hospital last night.

426
00:23:53,598 --> 00:23:54,850
Um...

427
00:23:54,933 --> 00:23:57,602
He told me the reason
why he pretended.

428
00:23:58,436 --> 00:23:59,855
Um...

429
00:23:59,938 --> 00:24:02,357
I know, um... We're stupid.

430
00:24:04,693 --> 00:24:06,611
Your brother loves you, boss.

431
00:24:07,571 --> 00:24:09,948
He did it to protect you.

432
00:24:11,449 --> 00:24:13,076
So he could...

433
00:24:13,160 --> 00:24:15,662
make up for what he did to you.

434
00:24:16,496 --> 00:24:18,707
[INHALES DEEPLY]

435
00:24:18,790 --> 00:24:20,292
Alright then.

436
00:24:20,375 --> 00:24:21,459
Go.

437
00:24:22,210 --> 00:24:23,628
Go get some rest.

438
00:24:24,254 --> 00:24:26,715
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING ON TV]

439
00:24:26,798 --> 00:24:27,799
Good night.

440
00:24:28,925 --> 00:24:29,968
Good night.

441
00:24:36,933 --> 00:24:43,148
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

442
00:24:49,529 --> 00:24:52,282
[ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING ON TV]

443
00:24:52,365 --> 00:24:56,620
[QUIRKY MUSIC PLAYING]

444
00:24:56,703 --> 00:24:58,038
[REMOTE THUDS]

445
00:25:17,974 --> 00:25:19,392
What are you trying to say?

446
00:25:22,103 --> 00:25:23,688
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

447
00:25:25,106 --> 00:25:27,901
[QUIRKY MUSIC CONTINUES]

448
00:25:27,984 --> 00:25:29,152
Uh...

449
00:25:31,446 --> 00:25:33,448
I'll just get some water.

450
00:25:34,157 --> 00:25:36,326
No, let me.
No, no, no, I'll do it.

451
00:25:37,869 --> 00:25:38,870
Uh...

452
00:25:39,955 --> 00:25:41,748
- My back...
- Do you want it cold?

453
00:25:41,831 --> 00:25:42,832
That's fine.

454
00:25:43,541 --> 00:25:44,960
- Thank you.
- [WATER POURING]

455
00:25:45,043 --> 00:25:47,629
My back's killing me.

456
00:25:47,712 --> 00:25:49,756
Probably from lying down
too much.

457
00:25:49,839 --> 00:25:53,468
I actually know a technique
that Mom used to do to Dad

458
00:25:53,551 --> 00:25:56,137
whenever he comes home tired
from meetings.

459
00:25:56,763 --> 00:25:57,764
What?

460
00:26:01,184 --> 00:26:02,686
Okay.

461
00:26:02,769 --> 00:26:03,770
Oh.

462
00:26:05,063 --> 00:26:12,070
[QUIRKY MUSIC CONTINUES]

463
00:26:17,284 --> 00:26:18,285
How is it?

464
00:26:18,910 --> 00:26:19,953
[EXHALES SOFTLY]

465
00:26:20,036 --> 00:26:21,371
It's okay.

466
00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:32,007
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

467
00:26:36,386 --> 00:26:37,637
Um...

468
00:26:38,430 --> 00:26:40,849
Should we watch something
to cheer us up?

469
00:26:41,808 --> 00:26:44,060
Okay. [CLEARS THROAT]

470
00:26:44,144 --> 00:26:49,858
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

471
00:26:49,941 --> 00:26:52,819
[WOMAN ON TV]
...the promise of better days.

472
00:26:52,902 --> 00:26:54,946
Because in the world of K-drama,

473
00:26:55,030 --> 00:26:58,116
one is given permission
to once again hope.

474
00:26:59,117 --> 00:27:00,535
Uh, Kim?

475
00:27:01,661 --> 00:27:02,662
Hmm?

476
00:27:06,875 --> 00:27:10,587
I just want to thank you
for giving me another chance.

477
00:27:10,670 --> 00:27:16,426
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

478
00:27:16,509 --> 00:27:17,510
[CLEARS THROAT]

479
00:27:20,347 --> 00:27:21,848
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

480
00:27:23,183 --> 00:27:30,231
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

481
00:27:47,123 --> 00:27:54,130
["HERE WITH YOU"
BY BINI PLAYING]

482
00:28:12,273 --> 00:28:19,280
["HERE WITH YOU" CONTINUES]

483
00:28:28,081 --> 00:28:30,208
Oh, boss, you're here.

484
00:28:30,291 --> 00:28:32,127
Wait, why are you
in work clothes?

485
00:28:32,210 --> 00:28:35,296
I'm ordering you
not to go to the office.

486
00:28:35,380 --> 00:28:38,049
You're leaving us
all over again.

487
00:28:38,133 --> 00:28:41,594
Ma, I did what I set out
to do here: to make amends.

488
00:28:42,387 --> 00:28:44,597
Now it's up to Brandon
if he can forgive me.

489
00:28:44,681 --> 00:28:46,224
What do you think about these?

490
00:28:46,307 --> 00:28:48,226
Sir, those are our bestsellers,

491
00:28:48,309 --> 00:28:49,811
especially for married couples.

492
00:28:51,020 --> 00:28:52,564
Perfect.

493
00:28:52,647 --> 00:28:57,193
Uh, we'll take these.
My wife here really loves it.

494
00:28:57,277 --> 00:28:58,194
Hmm?

495
00:28:58,278 --> 00:29:00,363
- Huh?
- Love, she's waiting.
